Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
When I select 'Female' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'MRI pelvic floor' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
Then I go to Page 08 of Pelvic MRI
And I click on 'Finding' radio button
And dropdown below 'Finding' is enabled

When I select 'Rectum carcinoma' from the dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is preselected

When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'T1: Infiltration submucosa/without safe infiltration of internal anal sphincter' radio button is enabled
And 'T2: Infiltration muscularis propria and internal anal sphincter' radio button is enabled
And 'T3: Infiltration subserosa and external anal sphincter' radio button is enabled
And 'T4: Direct infiltration into other organs' radio button is enabled
And 'TX: Primary tumor not assessable' radio button is enabled

And 'No anatomic reference' radio button is enabled
And '> 1 mm, CRM negative' radio button is enabled
And '≤ 1 mm, CRM positive' radio button is enabled

And 'Maximum extramural tumor extension' input field is enabled

And 'Extramural venous invasion (EMVI)' checkbox is enabled

And 'Narrow' radio button is enabled
And 'Medium' radio button is enabled
And 'Increased diameter' radio button is enabled

When I select 'T3: Infiltration of subserosa or perirectal fat tissue' radio button
Then 'T3a: < 1 mm' radio button is enabled
And 'T3b: 1 - 5 mm' radio button is enabled
And 'T3c: 5 - 15 mm' radio button is enabled
And 'T3d: > 15 mm' radio button is enabled

When I select 'T4: Infiltration of visceral peritoneum or direct organ infiltration' radio button
Then 'T4a: Peritoneum' radio button is enabled
And 'T4b: Organ' radio button is enabled

When I select 'T4b: Organ' radio button
Then 'Urinary bladder' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Uterus' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Vagina' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Sacrum' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Coccyx' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Levator ani muscle' checkbox is enabled
Then 'M. sphincter ani' checkbox is enabled

When I go to 'Characterization I' tab
And select 'Lower third' checkbox
And select 'Below/at same height' radio button
When I go to 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'T1: Infiltration submucosa/without safe infiltration of internal anal sphincter' radio button is enabled
And 'T2: Infiltration muscularis propria and internal anal sphincter' radio button is enabled
And 'T3: Infiltration subserosa and external anal sphincter' radio button is enabled
And 'T4: Direct infiltration into other organs' radio button is enabled
And 'TX: Primary tumor not assessable' radio button is enabled

When I select 'T4: Direct infiltration into other organs' radio button
Then 'Urinary bladder' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Uterus' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Vagina' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Sacrum' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Coccyx' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Levator ani muscle' checkbox is enabled
Then 'M. sphincter ani' checkbox is enabled

When I select '≤ 1 mm, CRM positive' radio button
Then 'Circumferential tumor location*' dropdown is enabled

When I click on any option from the 'Circumferential tumor location*' dropdown
Then an option is selected

When I enter '1' in the input field 'Maximum extramural tumor extension'
Then the number is accepted
When I enter '9999' in the input field 'Maximum extramural tumor extension'
Then the number is accepted

When I select 'Extramural venous invasion (EMVI)' checkbox
Then 'Narrow' checkbox is enabled
And 'Medium' checkbox is enabled
And 'Increased diameter' checkbox is enabled
